  "title": "Genetic control of hydrogen sulfide retention in Saccharomyces cerevisiae",
  "abstract": "The ability to retain hydrogen sulfide (H2S) inSaccharomycescerevisiae is under nuclear gene control. Mutants with the ability to retain greater amounts of H2S than the parent have been isolated and characterised.",
